  "story_title": "acknowledgements",
  "review_text": "[SPAN: display=block; fontsize=extralarge; fonttype=bold; text= Acknowledgements]\n\n[DIVIDER]\n[SPAN: fontsize=large; fonttype=bold; text=Becky]\n\nFirst and foremost, I wish to thank my wonderful wife for giving me the time, space, and encouragement to take on this sprawling, joyful, occasionally ridiculous project in retirement.\n\nNone of this would exist without your support, patience, and belief that this strange idea was somehow worth pursuing.\n\nYou've given me the freedom to dive deep into the longboxes, the history, and the storytelling that helped shape my childhood and still shapes my imagination today.\n\n\n[DIVIDER]\n[SPAN: fontsize=large; fonttype=bold; text=Fandom.com]\n\nMy thanks to the contributors at fandom.com ([CITATION: https://marvel.fandom.com]), whose collective work -- while occasionally imperfect or incomplete -- was indispensable in helping me reconstruct Marvel's early publication history.\n\nTheir issue pages and publication-week data provided the scaffolding I needed to verify credits, track continuity threads, and understand the publishing context of the era.&nbsp; This project stands on the shoulders of many anonymous archivists.\n\n\n[DIVIDER]\n[SPAN: fontsize=large; fonttype=bold; text=Comics to Astonish]\n\nA special thank-you to <b>Comics to Astonish</b> in Maryland ([CITATION: https://comicstoastonish.com]).\n\nThe owner personally helped me evaluate which of my books were CGC candidates and even handled the submissions for me (for a small and very reasonable fee).&nbsp; His expertise, patience, and generosity made a daunting process simple.\n\nLinking to his shop is the <i>least</i> I can do in return for the guidance he provided during a key phase of this project.\n\n\n[DIVIDER]\n[SPAN: fontsize=large; fonttype=bold; text=The Original Marvel Creators]\n\nMy gratitude to the writers, artists, editors, and production staff of early Marvel.&nbsp; Their work -- brilliant, chaotic, rushed, and often gloriously physics-optional -- is the foundation of everything here.\n\nThis site is, in many ways, a love letter to their creativity and their willingness to build a universe... <b>one deadline at a time</b>.\n\n\n[DIVIDER]\n[SPAN: fontsize=large; fonttype=bold; text=The Comics-History Community]\n\nThanks to the collectors, historians, scanners, indexers, and obsessives who continue to preserve comics history.&nbsp; From fan-maintained databases to long-running forums to the people who carefully scan brittle pages so the past doesn't vanish -- your work keeps the medium's history accessible and alive.\n\nIt's thanks to you that I still have digital copies to read of books I long ago parted with.\n\n\n[DIVIDER]\n[SPAN: fontsize=large; fonttype=bold; text=Readers and Fellow Travelers]\n\nTo everyone who reads these reviews, follows along, or shares their own memories of these comics -- thank you.\n\nYou help transform this project from a solitary archival exercise into a conversation.&nbsp; Your enthusiasm, corrections, questions, and shared nostalgia make the journey richer.\n\n\n[DIVIDER]\n[SPAN: fontsize=large; fonttype=bold; text=Future Contributors]\n\nFrom time to time, certain contributors will go above and beyond -- offering research help, donating materials, providing technical assistance, financial support, or otherwise making a meaningful impact on the project.&nbsp; When that happens, I'll thank them here by name (unless they prefer otherwise).\n\nLongbox Playback is an ongoing project, and this page will evolve with it.\n\nWhile I may not be able to call out <i>everyone</i> who offers me support, if you've gone above and beyond, your name belongs here."
}